      <p class="- topic/p ">This switch is to keep the engine’s speed from exceeding a limit.</p>
      <p class="- topic/p ">
         <fig id="fig_ec2_dvr_5gc" class="- topic/fig ">
            <image href="media/image225.png"
                   id="image_ic2_dvr_5gc"
                   placement="inline"
                   class="- topic/image "/>
         </fig>
      </p>
      <p class="- topic/p ">With the switch off, the engine reaches the maximum speed when the accelerator pedal is fully
      pressed. With the switch on, the engine’s speed is limited to a maximum rpm of 2,100. In the
      case where the vehicle is used mainly for driving, using this switch reduces fuel consumption
      by approximately 10%.</p>
